meta {
  name: Validate Merchant
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/validate-merchant
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  IntegratorId: {{sign_key_id}}
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "tokenId": 0,
    "actorId": "YOUR_ACTOR_ID",
    "machineId": "{{machine_id}}",
    "random": "RANDOM_STRING_FROM_NAYAX_27CHARS",
    "cipher": "BASE64_AES_ECB_CIPHER"
  }
}

docs {
  Direction: Nayax → Integrator (Nayax calls this on your server — or you call Nayax to initiate auth)
  Auth: IntegratorId header. The cipher is AES-256 ECB encrypted using last 32 chars of Secret Token.

  Cipher construction:
  - plaintext = EcomTransactionId (UUID) + "=" + random string (27 chars from Nayax)
  - key = last 32 chars of Secret Token (66 chars total)
  - encrypt with AES-256 ECB, base64-encode result

  On success: returns customDeclineCode = HashedEcomTransactionId
  Use that HashedEcomTransactionId as the validationKey in /initialize.

  Spec path: POST /validate-merchant
}
